h3. Problem Definition

Currently, there's no straightforward way to serve a localized message in Jira Automation.

h3. Suggested Solution

Provide a language dictionary so that the rule can refer to the target user's locale.

{code:javascript}
{
  "welcome.message": {
    "en_US": "Hello",
    "ja_JP": "こんにちは"
  }
}
{code}

Suppose {{reporter.locale}} returns the value of [GET /rest/api/3/mypreferences|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/api-group-myself/#api-group-myself], then the localized value can be referred by something like {{languageDictionary("welcome.message", reporter.locale)}}.

